OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 3 Jun to Fri 12 JunFLow
OL,6,Fpressure systems will continue to move
OL,7,Fin from the Atlantic, leading to
OL,8,Fshowers or longer spells of rain at
OL,9,Ftimes. The best of the drier
OL,10,Fconditions are usually more likely
OL,11,Ftowards the south and east, with more
OL,12,Ffrequent rain across the west and
OL,13,Fnorthwest. Drier weather may start to
OL,14,Fbecome more dominant through the
OL,15,Fsecond week of June. Temperatures will
OL,16,Fbe near-normal overall, with the
OL,17,Fwarmest spots most likely across
OL,18,Feastern areas. It will also be breezy
OL,19,Fat times, especially across western
OL,20,Fparts, and notably so around exposed
OL,21,Fcoasts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
